Migrated from EPA STORET Legacy Database- originally reported by Wisconsin DNR
West wind 8-10mph- cloudy sky- air temp 50
Northwest wind 5-10 mph- cloudy skies- crappies biting- air temp 79
Curly leaf pond weed to surface - 80% of the lake.
High water and bog work prohibited readings for the last 3 weeks
Southwest wind 5-10mph- partly cloudy- bright sun- .3" rain 8/3-8/5
Heavy rain turned the lake muddy.
Coontail and duck weed to surface- boating restricted.
The lake is 80% clear of weeds.
Last reading- lake is iced over as of 11/28/93.
Curly leaf pond weed covers surface.
Coontail to surface.  Assumed sample time was noon.
Public perception due to weeds.  Lots of duck weed.
Curly leaf covers 80% of lake surface.
Boating limited because of lake weeds.
Heavy rains-floating cattail clump in lake.
Cutting weeds = have boating lanes.  Water is bluish brown.
A lot of duck weed present
5 ft bottom by dam; high algae levels
5 ft bottom by dam; high levels of algae
Sunny with some clouds- no wind
Calm- sunny day.  Lake depth 6 ft
Cloudy- Breazy day.  Depth of lake 5 ft
Windy- Sunny- cool day.  Depth of lake 6 ft.
Sunny clear day.  Lots of curly leaf pondweed Sunny + clear day.  Lake depth 6 ft.  Lots of curly leaf pond weed.
Cloud.  Lots of Curly Leaf Pondweed- lots of floating dieing filamental algae- fish are spawnging.  Lake is 5ft deep
Cloudy.  Lots of curly leaf pond weed.  Lots of dead filamental algae floating.  Fish are spawning.  Lake depth is 5 ft
Mostly cloudy day.  Very storm week.  Lots of floating duckweed.  Curly leaf pondweed mostly gone.  Can see lots of filamental algae in the water.  Lake is 5ft deep
Sunny calm warm day.  Dieing filamental algae.  Lake level is 5 ft.  Lots of curly leave pond weed
Sunny breezy day.  5 ft water depth.  Water flow opposite of dam.
Sunny warm breezy.  Lake depth is 5 ft.
Cloudy-rained all day before.  Calm wind.  Lake depth is 4 ft.
Rained for 7 days.  Calm sunny day.  Lake depth 5 1/2 ft.
Sunny calm day.  Start of Fall.  Geese are grouping together.  Over 150 geese showing up on lake.  More Northern Milfoil than Eurasian.
80 degrees.  Very warm fall day.  Trees are changing color.  We have lots of Northern Milfoil as compared to previous years where the EuroAsian was dominant.
Very cold winter evening.  Checking O2 levels for winter information.
Over 2ft of snow-snow fall record surpassed this year.  Very bright sunny winter day.  Checking O2 level for winter observations.
Windy- warm @80 degrees. Lots of filamental algae- some curly leaf. Slight rain over night.
High thin clouds. Slight breeze. 78 degrees. Lots of native plants.  Three weeks ago there was sever flooding- floating bogs have broken loose.
Warm breezy day.  Cloud mix.  Fern Pond weed- coontail- northern millfoil was noticed.  Not much in the way of invasives.
Cool  sunny 62 degree day.  Native species prevelant- duck weed- lake not choked with invasives- open areas of water.
Breezy sunny 70 degree day. Hit bottom at 5 feet
Plants flowering.  Lots of fish jumping. Sunny calm day 70 degrees. Not many weeds. Some curly leaf. Cutters took time off because of fewer weeds. Hit bottom at 4.5ft.
Sunny calm morning. Lots of duck weed- filamentous algae- northern milfoil- coontail- very little curly leaf. Bottom is 5 1/2ft
Cool breezy and partly cloudy- lots of filamentous algae and duckweed. Water is 6ft deep.
Lake depth is 5 1/2ft. Clear skies- duck weed- Northern milfoil- coontail- saw large turtle and wax wing birds.
Sunny with partly cloudy skies calm day at 68 degrees. Filamentous algae- depth of lake is 5 1/2ft
Cloudy cool about 60 degrees. Leaves dropping. Depth of lake is 5ft. Very little curly leaf- few Eurasion milfoil plants.

Sunny- 72 degrees- slight north breeze. Lake depth 5ft. Filamental algae- small amount curly leaf- small amount Euroasian milfoild- duckweed- lots of fish. Healthy growth of coontail- NAmerican milfoil and wild celery.
Sunny- slight breeze- 62 degrees.  Lake depth 5ft.  Duckweed- filamental algae- NMilfoil and coontail coated with filamental algae. wild celery. Chinese mystery snails found by Susan Graham.

Stormed day before reads.  Lots of open water (none to few weeds in areas of Lake-unusual).  Slight breeze.  Duckweed- NMilfoil- coontail- wild celery- filamental algae- Chinese Mystery snails.  All plants coated with dead filamental algae.

10 inches of rain the past three weeks.  Dam has altered lake level from 6 inches below normal to 6 inches above normal the past week.  Mostly sunny and calm.  Lake depth 5ft.  Duckweed- Nmilfoil- coontail- wild celery.  Minimal Eurasian milfoil and curlyleaf.  All plants coated with dead filamental algae.  Lost lots of cattail bogs so downstream is 1/3 wider now.
Depth 6ft. Calm day- 80 degrees. lots of duckweed

5ft deep. Little amount of euration milfoild or curly leaf- lots of filamentous algae- more northern milfoil- coontail- celery lettuce but weed growth is sparse. DNR shut down cutting operation due to new cutters not following cutting plan.  Lazy Lake level being dropped due to dam repairs and cutting operation stopped due to low water level and end of year so cutters were pulled out of water.

56 Degrees- had rain on 6/10. Sunny + breezy.  Small amount of Northern Milfoil and Euroasian milfoil which is blooming- small amount of curly leaf- duckweed- filamental algae- lily pads- dead carp found and saw pan fish.  Depth of spot for testing is 5 feet.

67 Degrees and sunny- calm. Lake depth at test site 5 feet.  Filamental algae- Northern milfoil- some Euroasian milfoil- some curly leaf- duckweed- wild celery. Chinese Mystery snails- lots of the snails floating dead.  The invasive plants are very few.  Seeing lots of native species of plants- alot of Filamental algae coating the plants.  Seeing lots of pan type fish.
71 degrees- humid- hazey sky. Lake depth at site is 5 feet.  Coontail- Northern milfoil- wild celery- eldora- duckweed- filamental algae covering plants- dead Chinese Mystery snails.

75 degrees- sunny- slight breeze- calm.  Rained last two days. Duckweed- no weeds in cutting areas. Good amount of native plants- coontail- Northern milfoil- wild celery- filtamental algae covering plants. Geese and pan type fish.

74 degrees- sunny and breezy. 5 feet depth at site. Site between Lazy Point Rd and Oak Shores across from weeping willow. Duckweed- sparse amount of open water- dead Chinese Mystery snails- dead filamental algae- wild celery- coontail- Northern milfoil- eldora. Caddydid sounds.
Cool- breezy- fall like day- mostly sunny. Dieing duck weed- minimal weeds in cutting area. Can drive boat a long way without dumping weeds off prop.  4 1/2 feet depth at site.
Winter DO and temp readings only.  Clear sunny cool day.
5ft deep water. 54 degrees- calm and sunny day. Saw curly leaf- Euroasian Milfoil- coontail- eldora. Rained about 2 inches the past week.
72 degrees- sunny- breezy.  Saw curly leaf pond weed- edora- filamental algae- Eurasian milfoil- coontail.  Carp rolling on surface.

85 degrees- humid- breezy- sunny. 5ft water depth.  No rain- very dry.  Thousands of floating Chinese Mystery Snails- some empty shells and some shells still have snails in the shell.  Eldora- Northern millfoil- coontail.

78 degrees. Severe drought- end of heat wave. 5ft water depth.  Lots of floating Chinese Mystery Snails- some empty some full shells. Lots of total suspended solids in water- can't see bottom of lake.  Dead fish floating- counted 85 dead northern pike.

5 ft deep water. 72 degrees- hazy- had 2 1/2 inches of rain in 14 days. Severe drought. Duckweed- floating Chinese Mystery Snails some shells empty some full. Northern milfoil- coontail- celery plant.  Pan fish spotted.  Spotted Bald Eagle.
72 degrees- calm- sunny- severe drought. 5 ft water depth.  Eurasian milfoil- coontail- duckweed- northern milfoil- celery plant.

Drought- 75 degrees- suny- slight breeze.  5ft water depth.  Duckweed- celery lant- northern milfoil- coontail.  Can't see bottom of lake.  Very few weeds.  20 Grebes on lake- fishing slow- white lily pads-
Drought. 62 degrees and partly sunny- breezy. 5 ft water depth.  Coontail- northern milfoil- duckweed- minimal weeds- fewer floating Chinese Mystery Snails.

Drought. 57 degrees- sunny and breezy.  5 ft water depth.  Minimal weeds- northern milfoil- coontail- duck weed. Few floating Chinese Mystery Snails.  Grebes- and bald eagle.  Seeing variety of ducks.

Lake depth 5ft. Sunny calm day- 70 degrees. Duckweed- curly leaf pond weed- Northern milfoil- floating dead Chinese Mystery snails as well as live ones- geese nesting- 2 loons spotted. Beaver hut spotted.
Measure at 5 ft deep lake bed. Sunny calm (frost previous evening 31 degrees) Sauer Bridge depth 4.0. Turtles- goslings- Curly leaf pond weed- 1 deer- Filamental algae-

Sample depth of lake 5 ft. Overcast- calm with slight breeze- 71 degrees. Curly leaf pond weed- filamental algae- Coontail and Northern Milfoil. Saur Bridge reading 4.0 ft. Carp surfacing and rolling.
Lake depth of sample 5 ft. Sunny- calm with slight breeze- 64 degrees.

Lake depth of sampling 4.0 ft. Sunny- breezy day. Pelicans- few dead Chinese Mystery snails floating and some live ones. Duckweed- Curly leaf pond weed- Northern milfoil- Yellow and white lily pads- coontail- large leaf pond weed. Saur Bridge level 3.5 ft.

Sunny- 67 degrees- lake depth 5 ft. Northern milfoil- duckweed- coontail- A lot of harvesting being done- minimal amount of weeds in harvest area- turtles- geese and goslings- culy leaf pond weed. Saur Bridge water level 3.0 ft.

65 degrees- sunny- calm. Lake depth at sample site 5 ft. One week of no weed harvesting- minimal weeds in harvest area. Filamental algae- coontail- duckweed- Northern milfoil- celery weed- some curly leaf pond weed- Chinese Mystery snails- dead and alive. Saur Bridge level 3.0 ft.

66 degrees- slightly breezy- sunny. Sample depth of lake 5 ft. Duckweed- celery weed- Chinese Mystery Snails- alive and dead- Filamental algae- some Euroasian water milfoil- Northern water milfoil- coontail. Saur Bridge water level 2.8 ft.

Temp 65 degrees- overcast- mild breeze. Lake dept 5ft at monitor site. Northern milfoild- Coontail- filamental algae- celery weed- duck weed- Chinese mystery snails- minimal weeds in harvest area. Blue/green algae scum from Point to dam. Geese- deer- ducks.
64 degrees- 1/2 inch of rain previous day- wind 10-15 mph out of NW- partly cloudy. Monitor site depth 5ft. Northern milfoil- few weeds in cutting area- duck weed-

58 degrees. Monitor site 5 ft- partly sunny. Lots of duck weed- Northern milfoil- coontail- filamental algae- no weeds in harvest area. Blue/green algae from Point to dam. Geese- ducks- deer.  Jeanne from DNR set crayfish traps looking for swamp crayfish- no crayfish of any kind were caught in the traps.
Water depth at monitoring point is 4.5 feet. Breezy- 62 degrees- and hazy.  Baby geese- egret- ducks- turtle- 2 maybe 3 loons- snails- fish eggs- coontail- curly leaf
Monitoring area depth is 5 feet. 62 degrees.  Chinese mystery snails- baby geese- Swan- 3 comerants- about  100 carp mating in various areas of lake. Curly leaf- Northern milfoil.
Monitoring depth is 5 feet.  65 degrees. Celery weed- curly leaf pond weed- filamental algae- Northern milfoil- Blue flag iris- yellow and white lily pads- pond weed. Dragon flies

Monitoring depth is at 5 feet. 68 degrees and breezy and sunny. Chinese mystery snails- drangon and damsel flies- lightening bugs- frogs- and toads. Northern milfoil- coontail- celery weed- Eurasian milfoil- white and yellow lily pads.

Monitoring depth of water is 5 feet.  72 degrees- mostly cloudy- slight haze. Chinese mystery snails- chimney swifts- blue herons- dragon and damsel flies. Northern milfoil- filamental algae- celery weed.

Monitoring depth of water is 4.5 feet. 62 degrees- hazy to sunny.  White lily pads- duckweed- coontail- celery weed- large pond weed- bogs floating loose. Minimum weeds in weed harvest areas. Chinese mystery snails- heron.
Monitoring depth of water is 4 feet. 63 degrees- partly cloudy.  Duck weed- white lilies- coontail- minimum amount of weeds in harvest area. Blue heron.

Monitoring depth is 5 feet. 70 degrees- mostly sunny- rained almost an inch day before monitoring.  Duck weed- eldora weed- coontail- Northern milfoil- no weeds growing in harvest area and in other areas of lake.
Monitoring depth of water is 5 feet. Blue sky- sunny day.  Dead duck weed mats.  Weedless areas of lake in harvest areas and other parts of lake.
Monitoring depth of water is 5 feet.  Mostly cloudy day- breezy.  Some Northern milfoil- and coontail along shore lines.  Minimal weeds growing in harvest areas and other areas of lake.
Winter- 14 inches of ice.  38 degrees- breezy day- snow on top of ice is melting.

Heavy rain day before.  Sunny- breezy- 59 degrees- 7-12 MPH wind. Water depth at measuring point is 4 feet.  Minimum weeds in cut area.  Duckweed- filamental algae- curly leaf- Chinese Mystery snails.
65 degrees- sunny- breezy. 5ft depth at measuring point.Celery weed- duckweed- northern milfoil- curly leaf- white lily pads- minimal weeds in cut area.

Lots of rain- 5 inches before we went out to do measurements. 72 degrees.  Some sunshine- cloudy all around.  Duckweed- curly leaf- northern milfoil- celery weed- White lily pads.  Chinese mystery snails.
Rained 5 inches. 72 degrees.  Duck weed- Northern milfoil- Celery weed- White Lily pads.  Chinese Mystery Snails.

Cloudy- rainy day before. Swallows- Chimney Swifts- Blue Heron- Geese. Duck weed- Filamental algae- White lily pads- Northern milfoil- Euroasian milfoil- curly leaf- celery weed.   Swallows- Chimney Swifts- Blue Heron- Geese.   Lake depth at measuring site is 4 1/2 feet.
Sunny- 75 degrees. Had 6.5 inches of rain previously to this day. Depth of water at measuring site is 4 1/2 feet
Mostly sunny and 71 degrees- calm breeze. Green Heron- muskrats up Crawfish River.  Depth of water at measuring site is 5 feet.
Mostly sunny- calm wind- 71 degrees. Saw 2 Green Heron- 4 muskrats up Crawfish River. Depth at measuring point is 5 feet.  Duck weed- celery weed.

Partly sunny- 75 degrees- 8 MPH wind.  Depth of water at measuring site is 5 feet. Chinese Mystery Snails- lots floating- some empty shells and some shells have snails in them. Celery weed- Northern Milfoil- Eurasian milfoil- Duckweed- Eldora.  Minimum weeds in cutting area.
Mostly cloudy- 80 degrees- breezy had 1/4 inch rain night before.  Depth at measuring site is 5 feet.  Duck weed- Celery weed- Coontail- Northern milfoil- Chinese Mystery Snails.

70 degrees- partly cloudy- 8-12 MPH wind.  Depth at measuring site is 5 feet. Duck weed- Coontail- Eldora- Northern milfoil- Eurasian milfoil- pond weed- large and regular size. Saw snake swimming in water- 4 turkeys on shore- 4 Blue Heron around lake.  No Zebra mussles found at either Zebra mussel motel sites on Lazy Lake.
65 degrees- overcast day.  Depth of water at measuring point is 4.75 feet.  Duckweed- Fall leaves in water now- Northern Milfoil- Eldora. Geese flying with babies from this year.
5 days of 80 plus degrees. Strong thunder storms/rain storms. Gosslings- curly leaf- minimum weeds in cutting areas.  Depth of lake at measuring point is 5 feet.
60 degree temp. 6mph wind- mostly cloudy. Filamental algae- wild celery- duck weed- Northern Water-milfoil- elodia. Minimum weeds in cut area. Water level at measurement site is 5 feet.
78 degrees- humid- breezy. Duckweed- sago pondweed- dragon flies- damsel flies- wild celery- Eurasian water milfoil- Northern water milfoil. Water depth at measuring site is 5 feet.

63 degrees- breezy- sunny. Duck weed- wild celery- Northern water milfoil- Filamental algae- curly leaf- white lily pads- sago pondweed. Kingfisher- blue herons- deer- turtles. Depth of lake at measurement site is 5 feet.
Sunny- SSW wind 5-15MPH.  5 feet deep at measuring point.  Duckweed- Chinese Mystery snails- eagles- sea gulls- Euroasian milfoil- filamental algae-minimal amounts- curly leaf pond weed.
5 ft deep measuring point. 81 degrees- partly sunny- breezy. Curly leaf- Pond weed- Baby geese- dragon + damsel flies.
5 ft deep measuring point. 79 degrees- mostly cloudy.  Northern milfoil- coontail- celery weed- minimal weeds in cutting area. Saw Bald Eagle
5 1/2 ft. water level at measuring point.  57 degrees- partly sunny- breezy- 10-22 mph wind gusts. Northern milfoil- celery weed. Minimal weeds in cutting area.
5 ft at measuring point. Sunny- 70 degrees. Northern milfoil- Duck weed- White lily pads- Wild celery- Filamental algae- Coontail- Sago pond weed.

5 ft deep at measuring point. 73 degrees- humidity at 74- mostly cloudy. Duck weed- Coontail- Northern milfoil- Eldora- Celery weed- Filamental algae- curly leaf- White + Yellow lily pads- Pond weed- Canadian Geese- Blue Heron

Water depth 5 ft at measuring point. 70 degrees and sunny- breezy.  Duck weed- Filamental algae- Coontail- Northern Milfoil- Curly leaf- Damsel + Dragon flies- Egret- Swallow- Swifts- Heron- and Canadian geese.
Measuring depth 5 ft.  72 degrees- mostly sunny- breezy-5 mph.  Duckweed- Filamental algae- Celery weed- Northern Milfoil- White lily pads.  Chinese mystery snails.  Minimum weeds in cut area.

Water depth at measuring point 5.25 ft. 70 degrees- hazy.  Duckweed- Filamental algae- Coontail- Celery weed- White and Yellow lily pads- Curly leaf.  Pond weeds- Northern milfoil. Turtles- Blue Herons.

Depth at measuring point is 5.25 ft. 64 degrees- sunny.  Duckweed- Filamental algae- Curly leaf- Euroasian milfoil- Northern milfoil- coontail.  Damsel and Dragon flies- lots of minnows and fish in various sizes and species- turtles- Blue Herons- Canadian geese- Chinese Mystery snails.
Depth at measuring point is 5 ft. 62 degrees- sunny day- breezy wind out of SW at 8-10 mph. Minimum weeds in harvest areas.
Measuring depth is 4.5 ft. 8 mph winds- partly cloudy.

column1: 43 degrees. Breezy- sunny.  Readings taken 50 feet or so from Resort landing.

column2: GPS=N43 23.818- W089 02.455   Measuring point depth of lake is 5.5 ft deep. Over cast. Curly leaf- Duckweed- Filamental algae- white lilly pads. Chinese mystery snails. Swallows- Damsel flies- turtles- 1 deer.
GPS=N43 23.850  W089 02.426  Water depth at measuring point is 5 feet deep. Sunny day- breezy- 10-12mph wind. Curly leaf- minimal weeds in cut zones- white lilies. Goslings- deer

GPS= N43 23.813  W089 02.489.  68 degrees- sunny.  Coontail- duckweed- curly leaf- Fundamental algae- white lily pads- Eldora weed- celery weed. Blue heron- Geese and goslings- Bald eagle- dragon and damsel flies GPS=n43 23.813  W089 02.489.  68 degrees- sunny.  Lake depth at measuring point is 4 feet.  Coontail- duckweed- curly leaf- fundamental algae- white lily pads- Eldora- celery weed.  Blue heron- bald eagle- geese and goslings- dragon and damsel flies N43degrees23.813- W089degrees02.489   Sunny- 68degrees- Lake depth at measuring point is 4ft.  Coontail- Northern Milfoil- Duckweed- Celery weed- White pond lilies- Curly leaf- Filamental algae- Eldora.  Blue Heron- Eagle- Geese and babies- Dragon and damsel flies

N43degrees23.823- W089degrees02.465- Mostly sunny and 76degrees. Measuring point depth of lake is 5 feet.  Blue Herons- Damsel flies- Dragon flies.  Duckweed- Filamental algae- Celery weed- Coontail- Eldora- Northern Milfoil
67degrees- mostly sunny- wind is 5MPH.  Norther milfoil- Duckweed- Celery weed- Filamental algae- Pond weed large and small.
N43Degrees23.823'  W089Degrees02.459'   Measuring at 5 ft water depth. 72 Degrees- cloudy- 5MPH wind.  Duckweed- Celery weed. Northern milfoil- Chinese Mystery snails- Blue herons- swallows

N43degrees23.815- W089degrees02.467.  Sunny- 74degrees- 6MPH wind.  Water depth at measuring point is 5 feet.  Curly leaf- Filamental algae- Northern milfoil- Celery weed- Eldora- Sago pond weed.  Dragon and Damsel flies.  Chinese Mystery snails
N43Degrees23.821'-  W089Degrees02.473'.  Measuring at 4 1/2 ft. 62 Degrees- Mostly clear sky- 5-10 MPH wind.  Duckweed- Celery weed- Northern milfoil- Sago pondweed.  Chinese Mystery snails

Mostly sunny- 5-10 MPH wind- color change in trees.  Measuring at 5.5 ft water.  Duck weed- Northern milfoil- Celery weed- Sago pondweed- Lilly pads.  Chinese Mystery Snails- Minnows- Geese- Osprey- Turtles- dragon flies- 2 deer.
N43Degrees23.828'  W089Degrees02.448'.  50 Degree air temp- clear sky-10-15 MPH wind. Measuring at 5 ft water depth.  Osprey

37 Degrees outside- sunny- calm.  Inch is 7" thick.  Lazy Lake Fisherea is on- lots of ice fishing- snowmobiles- quads. 37 Degrees outside- sunny- calm.  Inch is 7" thick.  Lazy Lake Fisherea is on- lots of ice fishing- snowmobiles- quads.
37 degrees. Sunny- no wind.  7 inches of ice on Lazy Lake.  Fishing tournament on. N43 23.705 W089 02.552
34 degrees. N43 23.875- W089 02.373. sunny. 18 inches of ice on Lazy Lake.

56 degrees. N43 23.828- W089 02.450. Partly cloudy- windy 10-15 MPH out of west. Water depth at measuring point is 5ft. Curly leaf- Northern Milfoil- Filamental algae. Celery weed. Geese and babies- turtles- Dragon and damsel flies- Chinese Mystery snails.
71 degrees- sunny- clear sky- wind 6-10MPH. Depth of water at measuring point is 5ft. N43 23.814 W089 02.469. Celery weed- Duck weed- Curly leaf. Geese and babies- Dragon and damsel flies.
Mostly sunny- 72 degrees- slight breeze.  Celery weed- Duckweed- Coontail- White Lily pads. Goslings

N42degrees23.810 W089degrees02.472  Sunny- 75degrees.  Measuring depth is 5ft. Celery weed- Duckweed- Curly leaf- Coontail- Filamental algae- Yellow and White lily pads- Pond weed- Eldora.  Minnows- Damsel and Dragon flies.

N43degrees23.817 W089degrees02.439.  76 degrees air temp- wind 12mph SW. 5ft deep at measuring point. Celery weed- Duck weed- Curly leaf- Coontail- Filamental algae- White lily pads- Euroasian milfoil.
N43degrees23.819  W089degrees02.443.  70 degree air temp- 12mph wind out of NW- measuring point depth is 5ft- partly sunny.  Celery weed- Duckweed- Curly leaf- Coontail- Filamental algae
62 degrees air temp- clear skies- 10mph wind.  5 1/2ft deep at measuring point.
